wiki.summary: “No se ve” is the second .mp3 single from singer Emilia’s second studio album. It is a pop song that combines elements of funk carioca, electronic music and urban music. The production was done by producer Zecca, who presented the beat to the singer, who asked him to keep it exclusively for her. At the time of making the song, they decided to add a Brazilian artist due to the funk carioca sound characteristic of this country, so Emilia decided to contact the famous Ludmilla. wiki.content: “No se ve” is the second .mp3 single from singer Emilia’s second studio album. It is a pop song that combines elements of funk carioca, electronic music and urban music. The production was done by producer Zecca, who presented the beat to the singer, who asked him to keep it exclusively for her. At the time of making the song, they decided to add a Brazilian artist due to the funk carioca sound characteristic of this country, so Emilia decided to contact the famous Ludmilla. The song turned out to be one of Emilia’s most recognized songs globally, as it was a great success in several countries such as Brazil, Ecuador, Uruguay, Argentina, Mexico, Spain and also with the Latino population in the United States.
